                <h1>Understanding Discrepancies in Background Checks</h1>
                <p>The term "discrepancy" on a background check refers to inconsistencies or differences found between the information provided by a candidate and what is revealed during the check. This may include inaccuracies in employment history, education details, criminal records, or personal data. Such discrepancies can impact hiring decisions.</p>
